d": "1ASsPrfW9X", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 134, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "hunter", "id": 8618607, "raw_content": "", "author": "PillarOfWisdom", "created": 1778798789670, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "WeWillRideAgain", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsPrfW9X.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/TheJollyBrawler/status/2054772713592692854?s=20", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Awesome summary of the Chud the Builder situation ", "last_comment_created": 1778840065661, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 15, "score_up": 134, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": [{"width": 959, "heightRatio": 66, "url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HIQE4ZKakAAYvaQ.jpg", "height": 639}], "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 377, "created": 1778730965000, "id": "2054772713592692854", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2015265361445478400/o9DTJftS_normal.jpg", "displayName": "The Jolly Brawler", "username": "TheJollyBrawler"}, "content": "Today, @ChudTheBuilder was violently assaulted by a black person, and shot him. Many on the right have mixed thoughts about him. But...a few things: \n\n-Notice that Chud does not start the fights. He simply records what life is like in areas where public order has collapsed due to", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 8853}}, "post_flair_text": "\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\uddd1\ufe0f\u00a0\ufe0f GARBAGE PEOPLE  \ud83d\uddd1\ufe0f\ud83d\udd25", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsPsmog5", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 38, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8619239, "raw_content": "He pled the fifth during the congressional hearings and never faced any consequences. It\u2019s odd to me that he isn\u2019t discussed in a Ray Epps context. Perhaps some groypers will put it in context, lol", "author": "MAGATHREAD", "created": 1778823155889, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "OlivaireBandaloo", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Do people here know that Nick Fuentes was at J6 with a megaphone encouraging people to go into the capitol?", "last_comment_created": 1778828599580, "content": "<p>He pled the fifth during the congressional hearings and never faced any consequences. It\u2019s odd to me that he isn\u2019t discussed in a Ray Epps context. Perhaps some groypers will put it in context, lol</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 8, "score_up": 38, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2055087503259128125", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsPsmY1h", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 42, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8619191, "raw_content": "", "author": "DeepStateEnemy", "created": 1778820255187, "profile_picture": "IW9RHnbaEZJh", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "DefiancetillDeath", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASsPsmY1h.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/BenSwann_/status/2055087503259128125?s=20", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Data centers are paying reduced electricity rates while ordinary Americans are getting crushed.", "last_comment_created": 1778836207725, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 11, "score_up": 42, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 5, "created": 1778806017000, "id": "2055087503259128125", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1823184816948338689/J2NFvmEY_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Ben Swann", "username": "BenSwann_"}, "content": "But here\u2019s where the story takes a really dark turn: Data centers are paying reduced electricity rates while ordinary Americans are getting crushed.\n\nIn Georgia, some residents\u2019 who\u2019ve had AI data centers move nearby them have had their power bills skyrocket by as much as 267%.", "parentTweet": {"quotedTweet": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 0, "created": 1778713214000, "id": "2054698261038944640", "video": {"preview": "https://pbs.twimg.com/amplify_video_thumb/2054690681856122880/img/fDZWSBvAHrcGw4Yw.jpg", "mpeg": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2054690681856122880/pl/OGtonR4F9FtTvVrO.m3u8?v=136", "aspectRatio": [16, 9], "heightRatio": 56, "type": "video/mp4", "url": "https://video.twimg.com/amplify_video/2054690681856122880/vid/avc1/480x270/0u3Px3vNuLOKuOKK.mp4"}, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1823184816948338689/J2NFvmEY_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Ben Swann", "username": "BenSwann_"}, "content": "As AI systems rapidly expand, communities across America are seeing massive data centers suddenly appear near their neighborhoods. These facilities consume enormous amounts of electricity, water, land, and infrastructure resources, driving up utility costs, straining local", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 599}, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 0, "created": 1778805829000, "id": "2055086717955195072", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1823184816948338689/J2NFvmEY_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Ben Swann", "username": "BenSwann_"}, "content": "Between 3,000-3,500 new AI data centers are planned or under construction globally. They\u2019ll use a staggering 190 gigawatts of power.\n\nFor perspective, that\u2019s more electricity than many countries use. But they\u2019re not just using power. They\u2019re devouring water \u2014 as much as 449", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 306}, "likes": 86}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}], "status": true}